@node Utilities
@chapter Utilities

@defun http-server-url server &optional path &key protocol
Generate a URL for PATH on SERVER using PROTOCOL@. PATH defaults to @code{"/"}. PROTOCOL defaults to @code{"http"}. This is useful when the server was started with @code{:port t} and you need to discover the assigned port.

@lisp
(http-server-url my-server)        ;=> "http://0.0.0.0:54321/"
(http-server-url my-server "/api") ;=> "http://0.0.0.0:54321/api"
@end lisp
@end defun

@node HTTP Feature Summary
@chapter HTTP Feature Summary

http-server implements a subset of HTTP/1.1 as defined in RFC 9112 and http-server-ws adds WebSocket support per RFC 6455.

Supported:

@itemize
@item
HTTP methods: GET@comma{} HEAD@comma{} POST@comma{} PUT@comma{} DELETE and PATCH (RFC 5789).
@item
Request bodies: fixed-length (Content-Length) and chunked (Transfer-Encoding: chunked).
@item
Response bodies: fixed-length (string) and chunked (streaming function).
@item
Synchronous and asynchronous request handlers.
@item
Request targets in origin-form (@code{/path?query}).
@item
WebSocket upgrade (RFC 6455): opening handshake@comma{} text and binary messages@comma{} fragmentation reassembly@comma{} ping/pong@comma{} clean and abnormal close handshake.
@end itemize

Not supported:

@itemize
@item
The CONNECT@comma{} OPTIONS and TRACE methods. The server responds with @code{501 Not Implemented}.
@item
Request targets in absolute-form@comma{} authority-form or asterisk-form@comma{} as these are only relevant for proxy servers and the unsupported methods above.
@item
Header field values outside the visible ASCII range@comma{} since non-ASCII header values are an HTTP/1.0 compatibility feature.
@item
WebSocket extensions (RFC 6455 §9): extension negotiation is not implemented. Extension requests from clients are silently ignored.
@end itemize

